<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">I&#x27;m very grateful that we have a lot of players training LLM&#x27;s, including several that are published as open models and open weights.<p>I fully expect LLM results to start including ads, but because of the competition I hope&#x2F;believe the incentives are much better than they are for, say Google&#x27;s search monopoly.<p>It could potentially be more insidious though.<p>We&#x27;ll probably start sending prompts to multiple models and comparing the results with lower-power local models.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44370095&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44367084%2344370095" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
