<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">In the past you looking around documentation, SO answers etc would have hopefully helped you learn more about the tools and develop skills required to independently analyze the pros and cons. If you ask an LLM (or a search engine or a colleague) and take their words as the ground truth then you won’t develop the skills. Worst, sooner or later no one will have enough knowledge nor analytic skill to form an opinion on any sufficiently deep subject and they will all be dependent on corporate chatbots to spoon feed them information that may or may not be biased in a way against your interest. Now imagine if ChatGPT tells you to use azure and Gemini tells you to use GCP…</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44370337&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44367084%2344370337" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
