<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">My main use for LLMs is to ask it to give me some boilerplate configuration for some library&#x2F;tool I am not very familiar with and then look up the docs for the options it spits out. Like:<p>&quot;give me the terraform configuration for an AWS ECS cluster with 2 services that can talk to each other, with one of them available publicly and the other one private&quot;<p>Occasionally to give some small self-contained algorithms, for example:<p>Give me a way to format the difference between dates as human-readable text. For example: 1 day, 16 hours.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44368158&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44367084%2344368158" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
