<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">&gt; So now I&#x27;ve found myself much more likely to build personal projects because I know I can get past things that in the past felt a bit like quicksand to me.<p>I&#x27;m the opposite of you (my strength is in voodoo) but my experience is the same. Whereas before I&#x27;d spend 2-3 weekends getting bogged down on elements that aren&#x27;t my strengths and never complete, now I can easily whip up a mostly functioning web app (just for me) in just a few hours.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44368823&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44367084%2344368823" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
</table></td></tr><tr class="athing comtr" id="44368333"><td><table border="0">  <tr>    <td class='ind' indent='2'><img src="s.gif" height="1" width="80"></td><td valign="top" class="votelinks">
      <center><a id='up_44368333' href='vote?id=44368333&amp;how=up&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44367084'><div class='votearrow' title='upvote'></div></a></center>    </td><td class="default"><div style="margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:-10px;"><span class="comhead"><a href="user?id=alganet" class="hnuser">alganet</a> <span class="age" title="2025-06-24T17:01:56 1750784516"><a href="item?id=44368333">6 hours ago</a></span> <span id="unv_44368333"></span><span class="navs"> | <a href="#44367527" class="clicky" aria-hidden="true">root</a> | <a href="#44367816" class="clicky" aria-hidden="true">parent</a> | <a href="#44368823" class="clicky" aria-hidden="true">prev</a> | <a href="#44369993" class="clicky" aria-hidden="true">next</a> <a class="togg clicky" id="44368333" n="3" href="javascript:void(0)">[–]</a><span class="onstory"></span></span></span></div><br>
<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">A good reality check is: if a stranger asks you about a specific part of your toy project, would you be able to explain it?<p>If you can&#x27;t, it means there&#x27;s something there you don&#x27;t understand, and you lost an opportunity to learn. Of course, this is also true for reusing libraries and stuff.<p>Within a job, what matters is the _team learning_, and it&#x27;s roughly the same idea. At least one person in the team should be able to explain anything the team does. Trusting it to an AI puts the whole team in a precarious situation, even if it is something as simple as a CSS layout.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44368333&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44367084%2344368333" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
