<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">Toy Software is a lot like working on your bike&#x2F;car&#x2F;boat&#x2F;whatever.<p>Working on your bike is fun. Working on the bike you need to ride to work tomorrow is stressful.<p>I miss writing toy software. It’s fun. But inevitably I want to <i>use</i> said software and that’s where the trouble starts. You find all the bugs and none of the time to fix them.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44367321&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44367084%2344367321" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
