<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">I recently wrote my own invoicing application. I got wrapped up in the joy of adding the features I wanted. Many of these features come at a premium monthly fee for a big named product.<p>I needed to get an invoice out in a timely fashion. As much as I wanted to use my app, I found certain kinks I needed to work out (with styling, adding addresses, etc.) -- This was where I realized what you have articulated.<p>At some point, it becomes better to prioritize the &quot;fun&quot; in working on my bike, and the &quot;usefulness&quot; of the daily driver bike.<p>In doing so, perhaps the fun&#x2F;usefulness of each converges over time.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44367591&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44367084%2344367591" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
