<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">i am NOT saying they are not useful; they are. especially in domains you are unfamiliar with, or boilerplate, or when being used by an expert in the loop. but that is NOT the same thing as <i>being</i> an expert.<p>an expert can write 10 lines of code that will be hyper fast while an LLM will write 30 lines that are super slow. both &quot;will work&quot;, but one will fall over under load and will be hard to maintain and the other will not.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44371357&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44367084%2344371357" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
