<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">I quite enjoy the spirit of the article, and I believe joy in programming has become even more important in the AI agent coding age we&#x27;re leaving.<p>However, am I the only one finding those time estimates way too short?<p>I&#x27;m not the fastest programmer on Earth, but I&#x27;m not the slowest either, and I think most of those projects would take me a lot more time than those estimates, specially if I&#x27;d be working only 2-3 hours per day.<p>I feel most of those projects would take significant time researching and learning about the subjects, before even starting to code.<p>Example: recently I replaced my Pelican blog by my own hacky static site generator written in Odin, working 2-3h per day, it took me 2 weeks -- and this is a simpler project than many on that list.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44368936&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44367084%2344368936" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
