<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">Your project is vastly more specified than a toy project, because it has a real customer (you) who will expect it to work after it ships. That expectation is what separates toys from real tools.<p>I bet you could write a word processor in an hour. It might only add or delete one character at a time (no selections). It might persist only to a hard-coded &quot;output.txt&quot; filename. You might have to kill the process because there&#x27;s no quit operation. But that would suffice for a toy word processor.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44369192&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44367084%2344369192" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
