<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">This is the point, yes! Toy software is not production-worthy. It might not even be sufficient for your own personal use. It&#x27;s about building proof of concepts and rapidly scouting out the terrain of a field you don&#x27;t know much about, and getting a souvenir to remember the experience with.<p>Oftentimes I find that I enjoy one of the projects so much that I take it further than &#x27;toy&#x27;, but that usually ups the time estimate by an order of magnitude.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44371795&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44367084%2344371795" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
